<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE SPEED AXLE: SPICER - CLEAN AND INSPECT - INSPECT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="4">
        <title>INSPECT</title>
        <para>Prior to reassembly, inspect parts for signs of excessive wear or damage. Replacement of these parts can
            prevent premature failure and costly downtime.
        </para>
        <para>Bearing surfaces should be inspected for pitting, excessive wear, or overheating (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400729">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1400729" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400729" filename="../figg14/g1400729.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 29. Inspect Bearing Surfaces</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Inspect gears for wear or damage. Replace gears that are pitted, scored, broken or worn (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400730">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1400730" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400730" filename="../figg14/g1400730.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 30. Inspect Gears</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Inspect shafts for nicks or scores (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400731">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1400731" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400731" filename="../figg14/g1400731.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 31. Inspect Shafts</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Inspect all splines for wear, distortion from twisting, and cracking (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400732">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f1400732" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400732" filename="../figg14/g1400732.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 32. Inspect Splines</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
